%% DGM_Seq_HappyPath.mmd
%% End-to-end happy-path sync sequence (GL delta example)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant SCH as Scheduler
    participant EXT as ODP Extractor
    participant SAP as SAP S/4HANA
    participant K as Kafka
    participant TR as Transformation Engine
    participant LD as FinSight Loader
    participant FIN as Zetheta FinSight
    participant AUD as Audit / Wire-Tap

    SCH->>EXT: Trigger GL extraction (every 30 min)
    EXT->>EXT: Check RFC pool (<=50) and batch window
    EXT->>SAP: ODP delta request since last token (OAuth2 + X.509)
    SAP-->>EXT: Delta package (ACDOCA/BKPF/BSEG rows)
    EXT->>EXT: Persist advanced delta token (control DB)
    EXT->>K: Publish to domain.gl (partition = MC01/02/03)
    K-->>AUD: Wire-tap copy (lineage: SAP doc no)
    K->>TR: Consume GL event
    TR->>TR: Route by company code, map fields
    TR->>TR: Enrich currency (TCURR M), map V3 period, flatten hierarchy
    TR->>TR: Preserve CGST/SGST/IGST, run DQ validation
    TR->>K: Publish to load.gl (normalised)
    K->>LD: Consume load-ready event
    LD->>LD: Resolve tenant MC01 -> MERIDIAN-MC01
    LD->>FIN: POST /api/v2/journal-entries (Idempotency-Key=documentId)
    FIN-->>LD: 201 Created
    LD->>K: Commit offset
    LD-->>AUD: Emit lineage record (SAP doc no -> FinSight id)
    Note over SCH,FIN: Freshness achieved <= 4h (target 83% improvement vs 24h)
